Stillberg climate station. Location 46.773573N, 9.867160E. Data copyright SLF. The data set "stillberg_climate_1975_to_2007" contains data from the old station only (1975 to 2007). See "stillberg_climate" for a dataset combining both old and new stations (entire sampling period). Parameters: 
sw_radiation_incoming = incoming short-wave solar radiation in W/m^2; 
inc_sw_rad_normal_to_surf = incoming short-wave solar radiation normal to the slope in W/m^2; 
ref_sw_rad_normal_to_surf = reflected short-wave solar radiation normal to the slope in W/m^2; 
surface_albedo = diffuse reflectivity of the surface in %; 
hours_of_sunshine = number of hours (0 to 1) of sunshine received over the past hour; 
air_temp_fuehler = air temp in deg C; 
air_temp_basestation = logger temperature in deg C; 
air_temp_thygan = air temp in deg C; 
dew_point_temp_thygan = dew point temp in deg C; 
air_temp_100/50/10 cm = air temp at the given height above ground in deg C; 
soil_temp_100/50/10/0cm = soil temp at the given depth in deg C; 
relative_humidity_thygan = relative humidity in %; 
precipitation = sum of precipitation over 1 hour sampling period; 
snow_height = snow height in cm; 
wind_speed_mean = wind speed averaged over 1 hour (pre 2007) or 10 min (post 2007) sampling period in m/s; 
wind_direction_mean = wind direction averaged over 1 hour (pre 2007) or 10 min (post 2007) sampling period in degrees; 
atm_pressure = air pressure in mB; 
ozone = unknown units.

Stillberg climate station. Location 46.773573N, 9.867160E. Data copyright SLF. The data set "stillberg_climate" contains data from both the old station (1975 to 2007) and the new station (since 2007). For most parameters, there was a period of overlap when both stations were collecting data (approx. 27/10/2006 to 30/9/2007). During this period, sw_radiation_incoming, inc_sw_rad_normal_to_surf, ref_sw_rad_normal_to_surf, surface_albedo, air_temp_fuehler, air_temp_basestation, air_temp_100/50/10cm, and soil_temp_100/50/10/0cm in "stillberg_climate" are taken from the old station (sampling rate 1 hr) whilst all other parameters are taken from the new station (sampling rate 10 min). The different sampling rates mean that data points with the 1 hr sampling rate will not show up in gsn plots for this period unless the condition -inf to +inf is changed to (e.g.)-10000 to +inf because gsn plots the null values between data points. Parameter explanations:
sw_ radiation_incoming = incoming short-wave solar radiation in W/m^2; 
inc_sw_rad_normal_to_surf = incoming short-wave solar radiation normal to the slope in W/m^2; 
ref_sw_rad_normal_to_surf = reflected short-wave solar radiation normal to the slope in W/m^2; 
surface_albedo = diffuse reflectivity of the surface in %; 
hours_of_sunshine = number of hours (0 to 1) of sunshine received over the past hour (pre 2007) or over the past 10mins (post 2007); 
air_temp_fuehler = air temp in deg C; 
air_temp_basestation = logger temperature in deg C; 
air_temp_thygan = air temp in deg C; 
dew_point_temp_thygan = dew point temp in deg C; 
air_temp_100/50/10cm = air temp at the given height above ground in deg C; 
soil_temp_100/50/10/0cm = soil temp at the given depth in deg C; 
relative_humidity_thygan = relative humidity in %; 
precipitation = sum of precipitation over 1 hour (pre 2007) or 10 min (post 2007) sampling period; 
snow_height = snow height in cm; 
wind_speed_mean = wind speed averaged over 1 hour (pre 2007) or 10 min (post 2007) sampling period in m/s; 
wind_direction_mean = wind direction averaged over 1 hour (pre 2007) or 10 min (post 2007) sampling period in degrees; 
atm_pressure = air pressure in mB; 
ozone = unknown units; 
air_temp_rotro = air temp in deg C; 
relative_humidity_rotro = relative humidity in %; 
wind_direction_stdev = wind direction standard deviation over 10 min (post 2007 only) sampling period in degrees; 
wind_speed_max = max wind speed during 10 min (post 2007 only) sampling period in m/s; 
lw_radiation_incoming = incoming long-wave solar radiation in W/m^2; 
lw_radiation_outgoing = outgoing long-wave solar radiation in W/m^2.

Stillberg climate station. Location 46.773573N, 9.867160E. Data copyright SLF. The data set "stillberg_climate_post_2007" contains data from the new station (since 2007) only. See "stillberg_climate" for a dataset combining both old and new stations (entire sampling period). Parameters:
air_temp_thygan = air temp in deg C; 
relative_humidity_thygan = relative humidity in %; 
air_temp_rotro = air temp in deg C; 
relative_humidity_rotro = relative humidity in %; 
wind_speed_mean = wind speed averaged over 10 min sampling period in m/s; 
wind_direction_mean = wind direction averaged over 10 min sampling period in degrees; 
wind_direction_stdev = wind direction standard deviation over 10 min sampling period in degrees; 
wind_speed_max = max wind speed during 10 min sampling period in m/s; 
precipitation = sum of precipitation over 10 min sampling period, values are cumulative over 24 hours from 27/10/2006 to 1/9/2007; 
hours_of_sunshine = number of hours (0 to 1) of sunshine received over the past 10mins, values are cumulative over 24 hours from 27/10/2006 to 12/9/2007; 
sw_radiation_incoming = incoming short-wave solar radiation in W/m^2; 
lw_radiation_incoming = incoming long-wave solar radiation in W/m^2; 
lw_radiation_outgoing = outgoing long-wave solar radiation in W/m^2;
atm_pressure = air pressure in mB; 
snow_height = snow height in cm; 
soil_temp_100/50/10/0cm = soil temp at the given depth in deg C.
